The paper presents a learning algorithm for deep density models, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The algorithm is applied to Mixtures of Factor Analysers (MFA), which is a type of probabilistic graphical model commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the advantages of using deep MFA over shallow MFA, which relates to the topic of neural networks and deep learning (cs.NE). Finally, the paper mentions the use of factor loading matrices, which is a concept from information theory (cs.IT).
